Phikolomzi Mpambani, an investment banker, was shot twice in the head by unknown men at the corner of Bowling Avenue and South Road on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - The motive behind the murder of a businessman in Sandton this week is still unknown. The 38-year-old Phikolomzi Mpambani, an investment banker, was shot twice in the head by unknown men at the corner of Bowling Avenue and South Road on Tuesday afternoon.No arrests have been made.The police's Lungelo Dlamini has called on anyone with information to come forward. Police are continuing with the investigation into a murder of a person who was being followed from the back, at the moment, no one has been arrested. (Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)